After Chevron and Seibra manage to plug the Fabricator back into Agartha, Catherine is able to regain consciousness in the new exotic world.

—

The unnerving new reality of Catherine, in a place she doesn't understand and having lost all the anchors of her identity, she inhabits the body of a stranger (Seibra's) and even some faint crossed memories. Her depression takes a sudden crash.

There are plenty of Agarthians strolling the plain and elegant gardens of Agartha. A distant haze of white light obscures the horizon and skyline, making everything feel not only unfamiliar, but not quite real either. Catherine can walk as much as she wants towards the city in view, but she never seems to approach it.

The people are also uncanny, they don't point out how she walks naked. They don't even bother her for acting weird. Catherine feels invisible and takes some comfort in retracting into that shell.

Someone finally appears to recognize Catherine. Katarmaga doesn't understand her language, but she sure tries hard to appear welcoming and reassuring. She wears a strange ferret looking animal like a scarf and despite the elaborate bottom clothing, her bare chest makes the interaction feel awkward to Catherine. But who else could she trust to solve her situation? 

When the strange woman holds up a frame with Seibra's portrait, Catherine experiences the same jolt of recognition she witnessed from the woman.
It is herself... The picture feels like someone else, but this is who Catherine is living inside now. Dysphoria starts simmering, but this new woman must be able to provide the answers that are missing.

During a walk with the outgoing stranger, Catherine is encouraged to try talking about anything. It seems pointless, but Katarmaga points at objects calling them names and signals Catherine to repeat the same. It doesn't feel like much time has past, but the new friend opens as if the door to an invisible building and once entering, strings together some English words. 
"My room, your space."
Catherine is surprised at how fast the new friend appears to be learning her language and excitement rises that maybe she can get some answers.
Katarmaga sits Catherine on the edge of a bed, giving her a blanket, easing her anxiety. She sits in front on a pillow, on the floor with her pet. They attempt to introduce each other.

Katar.: "Name's Katarmaga. Your's must Visitor."
Cath.: "I'm Major Catherine, pleased to meet you..."
K: Much afraid for a big Catherine, how is Minor Catherine? *shuckles*
C: I'm lost, I'm not a visitor. Who are you? Where am I?
K: Wait, wait... I think I understand!
C: You do?!
K: You have irregular "be" particle word. I learned many languages, but old languages. Your's easier than first believed!
