They go back to sleep together. In Agartha there aren't security concerns, but Katarmaga feels the need to repeat how she can make sure Catherine is safe. Maybe there is time for a few last words before sleep...

K: "What sucks the most is finding out you aren't lesbian, you know."

A forced laugh is strained from Catherine and Katar chuckles back.

C: "Can I have some clothes for once?"
K: "Oh, you see, you know, being clothed in Agartha is so very formal. I like to get the message across that I'm pretty fancy, but in my room I never consider that a necessity."
C: "For how long have you been missing Seibra?"
