Catherine wakes up from the edge of the bed. The sun is as bright as when she went to sleep... She takes a dark device which becomes like a mirror by touch. Her body doesn't feel the same as she remembers, is it just sore from exercising on the last day? No... The face on the mirror is responding accordingly to her disturbed and anxious look, but the messed up hairstyle, the missing eyebrow, are the least strange things that seem wrong. This is not Catherine, yet someone next to her in bed starts calling her Catherine all the same.

Her memory clears... Yes, it's Katar, her host. Was she sleeping completely naked with me the whole time?! To be fair the room does seem pretty tight. Apart from a small annex and the exit, there aren't any doors. No kitchen, no bathroom, not even a TV... What kind of place is this?

Katarmaga doesn't allow time for all of Catherine's confusing thoughts to sink in...
Her English seems to have improved dramatically.
