K: "Sorry, that isn't possible. You were lost. Recycled, liquidated..."
C: "No! Don't talk like that about me, you are making me feel like... A thing..."
K: "What do you mean?... I'm sure you could make an avatar that looks close to what you remember about yourself, but I bet it will be easier to just make an improved version of yourself!"

Katarmaga sits beside Catherine and hugs her.

K: "I'm sure I can make you understand better with love, my friendly visitor.~"
C: "Is it okay to give you a secret kiss?"
K: "Kisses are always secret."

The two slowly and cautiously press their lips together, Katarmaga not holding back on stretching her tongue into Catherine before snapping back away from the kiss with her eyes closed and sighing.

C: "I'm sorry, Katar, if you were expecting I was Seibra playing some stupid joke and you had to..." *is interrupted*
K: "Shut up, I know you aren't Seibra. But... Who are you?... I mean... You are a Terran, I need to explain everything. I need to be patient. When you kissed me you thought you were starting something sexual or doing me some favour, but I actually needed to take reading of your psychological state and understand you. In Agartha, if you want to tell something secret to someone you kiss them. You also get how they are feeling and how they think."
C: "Were you trying to read my mind?!"
K: "Sush, not quite that, one thing at a time. I need you to realise that kissing makes a message come across much faster and more clearly than just talking..."
C: "You want to kiss me again?!"
K: "That isn't the problem. The problem is, I've never experienced such a low level of consciousness from a person, if that makes sense... How can you function, when your senses are so clogged and your thoughts so fuzzy?"
C: "I-I-I can't function... That's why I'm afraid of going out with you to do anything. I... I guess my mind only functions enough to keep my body alive."
K: "This is called... Depression, right?"
C: "I've always been a little bit like this. Did I hurt you?..."
K: "No, dear. You taught me something new. Learning always hurts a little."

The two girls return to cuddling and a tear runs down Katar's face. Seibra's form makes her feel so close to Katarmaga, but still, so far away. It isn't right for Seibra to feel broken and tired like this. Helping Catherine is a new life purpose and if someone like this exists in the outside world, how wrong have humans gone?

The next day, Catherine wakes up and is the first to shake her new friend awake. She has more questions... Not questions about all that is going wrong anymore, but what this new reality means.

K: "No, Seibra, I can't let you... Again... Wait! It's you Catherine, that's right."
C: "Yeah, you know... Tell me more about Seibra, please!"
K: "Seibra is pretty cool. A bad girl with an attitude, you see. Not many gals of her time are like that. She was a military man of the Agarthians, before we switched to cyberspace. So there aren't many people with physical combat experience like her and she rose to elite status."
C: "You say she was a military man?..."
K: "Yeah, she was born from in-vitro conception, rather than cloning like most Agarthians since her. So she was also born as a male. If you look around, there aren't males in Agartha anymore. As time went on, much like with Seibra, we just preferred being females. It started as a kink, it became a party trick of sorts, but soon everyone just accepted that the human female form is better and nobody has cared since then. It makes it easier when your technology and medical procedures only have to care about a standard body form."
C: "Wow, that's kinda freaky. Certainly I don't feel a lot manly in my new shell. I'm just like an athletic girl, I guess. But explain to me... Why am I missing an eyebrow?"
K: "Yikes, that's a bit of a gruesome story. Are you sure you want to hear?"
C: "Yeah, I need to know..."
K: "You see, in the beginning of the story, Seibra wasn't even considering being mind uploaded. It was a bit of a luxury and some people didn't like the idea. Some were afraid you were actually dying and whatever appeared in Agartha was a bad facsimile of the now dead person."
C: "Yes..."
K: "Manly Seibra, in her original body, was fighting war with the Puazi. Don't think about it. You wouldn't know them. What matters is that Seibra was entrapped and blasted right in the left side of the face. She became horribly disfigured. The bullets only penetrated her face, not the brain case, but her whole left side of the head caught fire and I hope she was knocked unconscious or it would have hurt a lot. Not much could be done. Doctors didn't want to wake her up from the comma. So maybe transporting her to Agartha would give her a chance in life and let her family hear a goodbye at least. Seibra could have just repaired her form to become flawless, but Seibra wears reminders of that trauma with pride. To remind her why she's alive all these years..."
C: "So even Seibra had an original body once..."
K: "Yeah, I don't have an original. I was born here in Agartha from a personality blend. If not by copying old consciousnesses and resetting their memory, this is how Agarthians are made these days. I don't know how long you'll have to stay here, but if you are to live in Agartha, you have to remember that the body is disposable and the mind is software."
C: "Seibra has lived to see many scary things. She must be really brave...
I have something hard to ask you. Is this part where we kiss to talk?..."

Katarmaga simply answers by connecting with Catherine's mouth right away, making sure an accompanying hug provides a sense of trust. Catherine learns in the moment how unnecessary it is to be unsettled by this gesture, which in Agartha carries only tender expectations. As the sheepish tongue of Catherine finds the relaxed tongue of Katarmaga, their minds meld and it feels like they occupy the same space of internal monologue.

C: "Should I live as Seibra now, if she doesn't return? Maybe accept my new body and identity?..."

It feels like a long while as Catherine learns this new method of communication. Insecure by whether she is doing it correctly and guided only by affirming emotions directly from Katarmaga's mind and heart. 

Katar releases the kiss, feeling that this answer ought to be said out loud rather than in secret. As our minds disconnect it feels obvious that only a couple of seconds were taken.

K: "No. You are your own person, Catherine. I would love to see a new friend grow in me. Someone with whom I can share the memory of the true Seibra. Do you understand that?"
C: "I'm sorry if I came across creepy... It felt right at the time. This is not what..."
K: "I know. Remember you've shared with me all your intimate perspective on Seibra and I agree it felt like it made sense during the kiss. It's fine. I'm glad you've learned so much these couple of days with me, and it's uncanny how you feel like you relate with Seibra. But I'm sure she's not lost. She is tough. Let's go outdoors and I'm sure I can show you things that will make you think more clearly!"

Catherine and Katarmaga walk in a park until they hunch over a bridge on a stream. Catherine feels uncomfortable with showing her face, and the impromptu clothing scurried by Katarmaga from unmatched sets, keeps being pulled up to hide the face whenever Catherine senses a stranger passing by.

K: "You know we should really go to a store to find better clothing, if you are to be overdressed like that..."
C: "Katar, I want to thank you for taking me in and being a good friend, even after you figured out I'm not who you thought I was."
K: "When you live like I've lived... Time never feels too long... Identity doesn't really matter anymore. Don't make me explain this with a kiss, please. 
After you arrived, I've decided to check the time again... It has been 60 years since Seibra left Agartha, but I feel confident I will see Seibra again."
C: "I'm so sorry! But I couldn’t have been transported 60 years ago! What gives?"
K: "I don't know. The Transporter records say that your trip took 20 minutes. And that scares me. I don't understand what has taken Seibra so long to travel if your transportation was simultaneous as the accident suggests. Maybe the Transporter lost power 60 years ago…"

Katar spoons around Catherine's shoulder trying not to cry.

K: "I don't know what that could do to someone... I don't want to imagine it. Being a physical person sucks so much! We can die and be mutilated every day and it's fine because the Fabricator will always rebuild you again... Make you healthier, younger, prettier, and even stronger if you need to. Hell, it will make a copy of you to help you defeat whatever is harming you. But you will never return from brain death and I hate it! I hate it!"
C: "I think it's my turn to give you some answers... Katar... Don't be upset."
K: "What must I ask to get the right answers?"
C: "So, my civilization had no knowledge of Agartha. Sure we heard these stories of legendary civilizations and ancestors to us physical humans, but it was oral tradition. Probably just stories... Then we found one of your people... 70 years ago..."
K: "Good grief, it was our lost maintenance girl. She didn't report back to Agartha about the end of the mission. That's why Seibra was sent out."
C: "What I know is that people outside are doing a sort of cold war. We are stalled in tactical superiority and the battlefield now is our minds, our perception of the enemy. My bosses wanted to extract some technological advantage from your agent a long time ago. I was asked to study some of your machines that were retrieved. I guess one of them turns out to be a Transporter. It didn't seem to work at all! I just sat on it and it gained life of its own. It grabbed me so tightly and it made me feel like I was being violated, but before I could react, my mind had fizzled away from the real world."
K: "Oh dear. You messed up so bad. The machine was in supply rationing mode. It needed to sacrifice you to materialise Seibra. That's an awful first experience being transported. If your mind wasn't so blocked out from your mental illness I might have been able to realise this sooner!
Imagine if the buffer had been rate reduced! You might have appeared in Agartha mentally handicapped or with a personality swing! That could have also happened to Seibra after incarnating!"

Catherine pulls Katarmaga into a tight hug.

C: "I feel that Seibra saved us both... I feel like she sent me a message in the form of her personal memories while I was in the machine and... It felt magical. But I wasn't in control and I can't make sense of these memories. It's all so hazy."
K: "It's okay, it isn't your fault. I should go to the Council to let them know what's happening. You need to be brave and come with me, okay, Minor Catherine?"

They take a few seconds to catch their breath.

C: "Is it probable I will become lesbian for you?"

Katarmaga laughs in relief. And they walk ahead...

K: "I only date people who know how to interface with Agartha.~"

They spend the rest of the day learning to read Agarthian and how to pull up multimedia and other objects from thin air. Next time they find themselves in Katarmaga's home, they quickly fall asleep, holding each other's arms in bed, not even taking time to undress.

A new day is upon us. Catherine still faces Katarmaga since they fell asleep together. They don't attempt to move, dozing on and off every sentence they trade.

C: "Katar... Why is the sun always in the same place?"
K: "Mmm... You've been glared a high noon this whole time you've been here? It's an option in your Agartha interface. I taught you how to..." *dozes off*
C: "Oh, I can make the sun and weather be whatever I want. Neat..."
K: "Whenever I wake up with you I wish to pretend I just had some hard partying with Seibra..."
C: "You said she loved someone else... Who are they?"
K: "Exfon is her name. I like her too. We've had sex. Unfortunately, she was also sent along with Seibra to the physical world. Different Transporter. If your people only..." *Dozes off again*
C: "Katar! Yeah?..."
K: "Oh yes, right... Your people only had one Transporter. Who knows what happened to Exfon, then."
C: "One more thing, Katar..."
K: "We can't 'one more thing'. We have to get up and do things..."
C: "Is it normal that I have an urge to kiss you?"

Katarmaga's eyes spring wide open breaking the sleepy spell.

K: "Well, I guess that once you learn how things are done in Agartha you can't help but prefer to communicate the easier way."
C: "But do you feel the need to send me a picture or an emotion right now?"
K: "All I feel like sending you, you already know."
C: "I think that my team will try doing what they can to retrieve me. Maybe I will not stay for much longer. Do you think they have a chance?"
K: "I don't know. They probably need Seibra's help out there. The devices won't work on all the males swarming your world."
C: "Yeah, that may be a problem..."
K: "It depends on how much they let Seibra work. The odds are against us, right? I mean, they saw a machine transform you into... Well this person that you are now, except she can't speak your language. I wouldn't fault them if they were scared of what you've become, or what they believe you did, even though it's a different person. I'm afraid Seibra might be more temperamental than you and will cause some misunderstanding."
C: "I think you've shown me that this is my world now, not that place outside. I thought it was scary to be here because I didn't know what to expect. But out there everyone expects something of me and I can't handle it. You always tell me things aren't my fault and you make me feel secure no matter what I look like. No matter how I'm feeling..."
